.Dd 2026-07-20
.Dt SLOWCAT 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm slowcat
.Nd print files at a limited rate
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl s Ar baud
.Op Ar
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
reads each
.Ar file
(or standard input when no
.Ar file
is given, or when
.Ar file
is
.Sq - )
and writes the bytes to standard output, sleeping between small chunks so
that the average rate approximates the configured baud rate.
.Pp
The chunk size is clamped to between 1 and 128 bytes; the inter-chunk delay
is sized so that the average throughput matches the configured baud rate.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl s Ar baud
Target rate in bits per second.
Defaults to 9600.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It 0
All files were printed successfully.
.It 2
At least one file could not be opened; remaining files were still processed.
.It 1
Invalid
.Fl s
argument.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Emit a log at 300 baud:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ slowcat -s 300 /var/log/messages
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr cat 1
